String toUpperCase() method in java

String toUpperCase method or touppercase java have two variants.

public String toUpperCase()
public String toUpperCase(Locale locale)

java string touppercase converts a string to uppercase letters. Here’s String toUpperCase() method example or java program to convert string into uppercase.

public class StringToUppercaseDemo
{
   public static void main(String[] args)
   {
      String str = "hello world";
      String strUpper = str.toUpperCase();
      System.out.println(strUpper);
   }
}


Output:

HELLO WORLD

Whereas toUpperCase(Locale loc) converts all the characters to uppercase using the rules of the given Locale.

public String toUpperCase(Locale locale)

Now let’s see java String toUpperCase(Locale loc) method example.

import java.util.Locale;
public class ToUppercaseLocaleDemo
{
   public static void main(String[] args)
   {
      String str = "i love java";
      String strTurkish = str.toUpperCase(Locale.forLanguageTag("tr")); 
      String strEnglish = str.toUpperCase(Locale.forLanguageTag("en")); 
      System.out.println(strTurkish); 
      System.out.println(strEnglish);
   }
}


Output:

? LOVE JAVA
I LOVE JAVA
